cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with dynamic graph algorithms, specifically for the problem of graph coloring. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also involves computational geometry (cs.CG) as it deals with planar graphs, and graph theory (cs.GT) as it studies arboricity. Finally, the paper discusses lower bounds (cs.CC) and initiates the study of implicit dynamic colorings, which is a topic related to computational complexity.
